I reminisce over our endless night rythm, dancing and learning 
to speak through to each others hearts

two languages of the same branch, with just enough overlap to 
hint at the depth behind words that never say quite enough

I think back to that moment, the last one with you.
You walked away, and i watched your back, until shame drove me to turn mine

Nobody was at fault.
Nothing happened between us, you were overwhelmed
You needed something, and couldnt speak my way enough to ask for help

You craved what i now know to be comfort
I gave what i hope you know to be respect
You heard that i left, I said that I'll always be here
